Since you bring up my Alma Mater, I can’t help but chime in. First, Amherst College was named after the Town, not the man per se.  Although there is no evidence that small-pox infested blankets were ever actually distributed to native peoples, there is good evidence that Lord Jeff advocated this tactic. Per UMass Emeritus Professor Peter d’Errico, Amherst’s actual words written in quill pen were, “You will Do well to try to inoculate the Indians by means of Blankets, as well as to try Every other method that can serve to Exterpate this Excrable Race.” I should also mention that in 1941, the then college president Stanley King ordered custom china for the newly built Valentine Dining Hall which had a “Lord Jeff chasing Indian” theme. These were in use until 1973 when they were silently, without official comment, removed from service. I was a freshman that year and was able to “acquire” a full set before they were gone. In 2016 the trustees (wisely and appropriately) agreed to change the mascot and the announcement of the mammoth was made in April 2017. You can see the some of this history and the old plates here:

